FAIL_TO_PASS: when unknown option and showSuggestionAfterError() then show suggestion
when may be duplicate identical candidates then only return one
when subcommand option then candidate for subcommand option suggestion
when digit option defined and command-argument is --1 then negative not consumed
when cli of --1234567 and options ["--1234567890"] then suggest --1234567890 because 3 edits away is similar for long string
when cli of --cat and options ["--at"] then suggest --at because 1 deletion
when default help option then --help is candidate for suggestion
when cli of --bat and options ["--cat"] then suggest --cat because 1 substitution
when cli of --act and options ["--cat"] then suggest --cat because 1 transposition
when cli of --xat and options ["--rat","--cat","--bat"] then suggest --bat, --cat, --rat because sorted possibles
when cli of --cart and options ["--camb","--cant","--bard"] then suggest --cant because only closest of different edit distances
when cli of --a and options ["--ab"] then suggest --ab because one edit away
when custom help option then --custom-help is candidate for suggestion
when cli of --caxx and options ["--cart"] then suggest --cart because 2 edits away and longer string
when global option then candidate for subcommand option suggestion
when global and local options then both candidates
when digit option defined and option-argument is --1 then negative not consumed
when cli of --at and options ["--cat"] then suggest --cat because 1 insertion
